{{Quote|So, where should we send Norky?''"<br />"''How about the Lightning Forest? He'll be burned to a crisp!|Wicket Wystri Warrick and Latara|<ref name="Bringing Up Norky" />}}
The '''Lightning Forest''' was a dangerous location on the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]]. The [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] [[Logray/Legends|Logray]] owned a [[Logray's globe|globe]] of Endor that depicted the Lightning [[Forest/Legends|Forest]] as a cluster of [[Tree/Legends|trees]] that crackled with electricity.<ref name="Bringing Up Norky" /> In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="Date note">{{InsiderCite|23|Star Wars Publications Timeline|''Star Wars'' Publications Timeline}} dates the events of the [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] animated series, which include the appearance of the Lightning [[Forest/Legends|Forest]] in "[[Bringing Up Norky]]," to three [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after the events of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], which corresponds to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> the young Ewoks [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket Wystri Warrick]], [[Latara/Legends|Latara]], [[Teebo/Legends|Teebo]], and [[Kneesaa a Jari Kintaka/Legends|Kneesaa a Jari Kintaka]] used Logray's globe to search for a place to send [[Norky]], a troublesome child who was staying in their [[Bright Tree Village/Legends|village]]. Looking at the globe, Latara suggested sending Norky to the Lightning Forest, claiming that [[Gender/Legends|he]] would be "[[Fire/Legends|burned]] to a crisp." Teebo alternatively suggested the [[Molten Mountains]]. Finally, Kintaka suggested the [[Vacant Valley]], reminding the group that they were just trying to relocate Norky, not bring him physical harm.<ref name="Bringing Up Norky" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Lightning Forest first appeared in "[[Bringing Up Norky]],"<ref name="Bringing Up Norky" /> the nineteenth episode in the [[Ewoks: Season Two|second season]] of the animated television series [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']].<ref name="Insider 27">{{InsiderCite|27|A Star Wars CELibration|A ''Star Wars'' CELibration}}</ref> The episode was written by [[Bob Carrau]] and [[Earl Kress]],<ref name="Bringing Up Norky" /> and it premiered on [[November 22]], [[1986]].<ref name="Insider 27" />

